article.description: — Omari Moore scored 19 points as San Jose State beat Alabama State 70-57 on Tuesday.
article.headline: Moore scores 19 as San Jose State tops Alabama State 70-57
article.linkText: Moore scores 19 as San Jose State tops Alabama State 70-57
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calf. -- — Omari Moore scored 19 points as San Jose State beat Alabama State 70-57 on Tuesday. Moore added five rebounds for the Spartans (3-0). Alvaro Cardenas Torre hit three 3-pointers and scored 17. Isaiah Range led the way for the Hornets (0-4) with 18 points. Alex Anderson added 10 points, while Antonio Madlock scored nine. San Jose State carried a slim three-point lead into halftime, as Moore led the way with 13 points. NEXT UP Up next for San Jose State is a matchup Thursday with Hofstra at home. Alabama State visits Pittsburgh on Sunday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
